Not yet automated.

Simple test using tinyproxy as the forward proxy.
All processes on same machine using loopback.

1. Start tinyproxy

  $ tinyproxy -c irlproxy.conf -d

2. in another shell start router2

  $ skrouterd -c r2w4.conf

3. in another shell start router1

  $ skrouterd -c r1w4.conf

4. Note 3 happy inter router links.

5. terminate router2, watch router1 reconnect failures with error from proxy.

6. restart router2 and note links reestablished.
